summaries.short: Season One Finale. Will's future at ACN is jeopardized by a damning revelation; Jim and Maggie reach a crossroad.
summaries.full: Season One Finale. Nina Howard surprises Mac with a damning revelation; Jim and Maggie reach a crossroad; Sloan weighs a new job offer; Neal uses his internet alter-ego to smoke out a threat. Will, Mac, and Charlie face off with Leona and Reese during a tension-filled lunch meeting.

summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. Will and the staff are questioned by their lawyer about an ACN story that's become a network crisis.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. Will and the News Night staff are questioned by their lawyer about a story they've aired that's become a network crisis. An on-air remark from Will has him pulled from 9/11 anniversary coverage. Jim volunteers to cover for an embed reporter on the Romney campaign, and Neal investigates the beginnings of Occupy Wall Street.

summaries.short: Will and Mac are forced to abandon their principles in order to boost ratings and land a Republican debate.
summaries.full: News Night's refusal to lead with a pair of sensational stories causes ratings to plummet--and forces Will and Mac to abandon their principles in order to lure back viewers and shore up the network's bid to land a Republican debate. Meanwhile, Will auditions an unlikely scribe, Brian Brenner, to write an all-access profile; and Sloan chafes over a lack of air time on a story.

summaries.short: The staff's anniversary party is cut short when they learn the President will be making an impromptu national address.
summaries.full: An anonymous source contacts Charlie and provides advance details on an imminent story of national importance. When news breaks that the President will be making a televised speech that night, the 2.0 staff cuts short its one-year (and one week) anniversary party, and rushes back to the newsroom amidst a flurry of speculation as to what exactly happened.
